      "content": {
        "title": "Non-Accidental Trauma and Child Abuse Recognition",
        "definition": "Suspicious injury patterns including metaphyseal corner fractures, posterior rib fractures, and inconsistent history requiring mandatory reporting.",
        "summary": "Ten-four-fifty rule and multiple injuries at different stages raise concern. Skeletal survey in infants."
      },
